# Defense & Detection Mechanisms

## Defense Matrix (6D)

| Action | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| **Detect** | Identify malicious activity. |
| **Deny** | Prevent the attack. |
| **Disrupt** | Interrupt the attack. |
| **Degrade** | Reduce the attack's effectiveness. |
| **Deceive** | Mislead the attacker (e.g., Honeypots). |
| **Destroy / Contain** | Isolate infected systems and stop the attack. |

---

## Defense by Kill Chain Stage

| Stage | Detection | Prevention |
|--------|-----------|------------|
| **Reconnaissance** | Firewall/IDS logs, scan detection | Firewall rules, hide unnecessary information |
| **Weaponization** | Malware analysis, Threat Intelligence | Generate IoCs |
| **Delivery** | Email Gateway, user reports | SPF, DKIM, DMARC, URL filtering, attachment scanning |
| **Exploitation** | EDR, WAF | Patch management, DEP, ASLR, Input Validation |
| **Installation** | FIM, Registry monitoring | Least Privilege, AppLocker |
| **C2** | Beaconing, DNS analysis, Proxy/Firewall logs | DNS Sinkhole, Egress Filtering, Network Segmentation |
| **Actions on Objectives** | DLP, UEBA | Isolation, Encryption, Backups |

---

# Important Log Sources (SOC)

| Log Source | Detects |
|------------|----------|
| **Firewall / Proxy** | Malicious domains, C2 traffic, Beaconing |
| **Email Gateway** | Phishing, malicious attachments |
| **EDR / Antivirus** | Exploitation, malware, persistence |
| **DNS Logs** | DGA, DNS Tunneling |
| **Active Directory** | Brute Force, Pass-the-Hash, Privilege Escalation |

